<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>ACLU Press Release  07/19/96: ACLU Urges FDA to Approve Mifepristone 
for Early Medical Abortion  Statement of Janet Gallagher, Director ACLU's
Reproductive Freedom Project
</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff">
<BLOCKQUOTE><IMG SRC="/graphics/pressrel.gif">
<CENTER>
<H2>ACLU Urges FDA to Approve Mifepristone for Early Medical Abortion:
Statement of Janet Gallagher, Director ACLU's Reproductive Freedom Project</H2></CENTER>
<P> <B>FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE<BR>July 19, 1996</B></P>
<P>WASHINGTON -- For more than a decade, American women have been denied the
option of safe and effective nonsurgical abortions because of vocal protests
from anti-choice extremists.  The Food and Drug Administration now has the
opportunity to approve Mifepristone, and provide women with an important new
option of early medical abortions. 
</P>
<P>The ACLU's Reproductive Freedom Project calls upon the FDA to act
immediately on the application to approve Mifepristone and make early medical
abortions available to women in this country by the end of the year.   Women
should have access to all surgical and nonsurgical abortion procedures that have
proven safe and effective. 
</P>
<P>Mifepristone has long been established as a safe and effective alternative
to surgical abortions.  Hundreds of thousands of women in other counters have
used Mifepristone for years without major side effects or complications.
Clinical trials held in the U.S. have reached similar conclusions. 
</P>
<P>Unfortunately, anti-choice extremists are attempting to mislead the public
with exaggerated and unsubstantiated claims about Mifepristone's safety.  Their
assertions are perhaps best left to the physicians with intimate knowledge of
the medical procedure, but it is worth noting that those claims have been
roundly  rejected by the medical and public health community. 
</P>
<P>These same anti-choice groups who are opposing FDA approval of Mifepristone
have also been trying to criminalize late-term abortion procedures.  The irony
is telling: after doing their best to ban late-term abortion, they are now
directing their efforts to ban early medical abortions.  They are not fooling
anybody with their thinly-veiled agenda. Their opposition to Mifepristone stems
from their strategy to outlaw all abortions. 
</P>
<P>Women who want to avoid surgery should have access to safe and effective
early medical abortions.  The FDA should fulfill their public health mission and
move quickly to approve Mifepristone.</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<CENTER><A HREF="/graphics/toolbar.map"><IMG
SRC="/graphics/toolbar.gif" ISMAP="ISMAP" BORDER="0"></A>
<P></P>
<H6><I>Copyright 1996, The American Civil Liberties Union</I></H6></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
