<HEAD>
<TITLE> Barry Steinhardt</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF>
<blockquote>
<img src="/graphics/abouthdr.gif"><h2>Barry Steinhardt - Associate Director of the ACLU</h2>
<img src="/graphics/stein.jpg">
<br clear=all>
<P>
Barry Steinhardt is the Associate Director of the National Office of the American Civil Liberties
Union (ACLU) and Chair of ACLU's Cyber Liberties Task Force.  As Associate Director of the
ACLU, Steinhardt has primary responsibility for the  development of organizational policy and
National office assistance in the organizational development of the ACLU's state affiliates..
<P>
As Chair of the ACLU's Cyber Liberties Task Force, Steinhardt has helped to coordinate the
ACLU's campaigns to keep Cyberspace free from censorship, and to oppose the Clipper Chip,
digital telephony and other governmental assaults on privacy in the information age.
<p>
  Mr. Steinhardt previously served as Executive Director of the ACLU affiliates in Pennsylvania
and Vermont.  He also served as Director of the Vermont Public Interest Research
Group(VPIRG). 
<p>
Mr. Steinhardt has authored articles in a variety of publications including Business and Society
Review, U.S.A. Today, Net Guide, The New York Daily News, The Philadelphia Inquirer and the
Pittsburgh Post Gazette.
<p>
He recently served on the United States Delegation to the 1995 OSCE Conference on
Non-Governmental Organizations in Warsaw Poland.
<p>
Barry Steinhardt earned a J.D. at the Northeastern University School of Law.
</blockquote>

