		<HEAD>	
		<TITLE>Fight Discrimination against Gays and Lesbians
</TITLE>
		</HEAD>
		<BODY bgcolor="#ffffff">
		<BLOCKQUOTE><IMG SRC="/graphics/actionhdr.gif">

<center><img align="right" src ="/graphics/actnow.gif"><font face="Arial" size="+2" color="#000080">Fight Discrimination against Gays and Lesbians
</font></center>
<blockquote><font size = +2>T</font>
 he Employment Non-Discrimination Act is the most important piece of gay rights legislation currently in Congress.  The legislation - also known as ENDA - would outlaw discrimination based on sexual orientation in the workplace. In the last Congress, ENDA was considered in the Senate and failed by a vote of 49 to 50.  This Congress we will redouble our efforts to get this legislation passed.</blockquote>
<center><font face="Arial" size="+2" color="#000080">Support This Legislation</font></center>
<p>
<img src = "/graphics/redstar.gif">In 41 states it is perfectly legal to fire someone because of their real or perceived sexual orientation.  We believe that people should be judged at work by their performance, not by anything in their private lives.

<p>
<img src = "/graphics/redstar.gif">Polls consistently show that most Americans oppose workplace discrimination. A May 1996 Newsweek poll found that 84 percent of Americans support equal rights for gays in the workplace and a June 1996 Associated Press poll found that 85 percent of Americans with the same opinion.

<p>
<img src = "/graphics/redstar.gif">ENDA does not call for any special treatment for gays and lesbians, and excludes religious institutions, the military and businesses with less than 50 employees.


