<TITLE>Eye on the Opposition</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF>
<blockquote>
<img src="/graphics/abouthdr.gif"><CENTER><h1>Eye on the Opposition </h1></CENTER>
On Wednesday, May 17, the Christian Coalition released its<A HREF="/about/summary.html"> Contract with the American Family</A>, which it called a "bold agenda to strengthen the family and restore common-sense values."
<P>
Surrounded by the House Republican leadership, including Speaker Newt
Gingrich and Majority Leader Dick Armey, officials of the Christian Coalition
said that their Contract contained ten proposals that "will hold government
accountable for the cultural crisis that has afflicted our nation over the
past three decades."
<P>
On Monday, the ACLU sent a <A HREF="/about/aclultr.html">letter to President Clinton</A>, all Members of Congress and the 50 state governors, urging them to reject the Christian
Coalition's proposals to tamper with the Constitution. The letter focused on
the Contract's centerpiece: a proposal for an amendment that would, if
adopted by Congress and the states, would inevitably lead to the
reintroduction of organized school prayer.
<P>
On Wednesday, the ACLU released a brief analysis of the Contract, saying that
contained "radical ideas," that Congress should reject. "The Christian
Coalition says that its contract is an agenda to restore common-sense values
in America," ACLU Washington Office Director Laura Murphy Lee said. "In
reality, however, the Christian Coalition's Contract would, if enacted by
Congress, mean a radical shift toward government control of the most personal
elements of American life."     <P>
<h3><a href="/about/summary.html">The Contract with the American Family </a><br>
<a href="/about/reedsmt.html">Ralph Reed on the Contract</a><br>
<a href="/about/leader.html">House Majority Leader on the Contract</a><br>
<a href="/about/aclultr.html">Ira Glasser's Letter to President Clinton</a><br>
<a href="/about/relstuds.html">Letter to ABA</a><br>
<a href="/news/n051595b.html">May 15th ACLU Press Release</a><br>
<a href="/news/n051795.html">May 17th ACLU Press Release</a></h3>
</blockquote>




<CENTER><A HREF="/graphics/toolbar.map"><IMG SRC="/graphics/toolbar.gif" ISMAP BORDER=0></A><P>
